Fix behavior of fake os.makedirs

- use a similar implementation as the real fs

[pre-commit.ci] pre-commit autoupdate

updates:
- [github.com/astral-sh/ruff-pre-commit: v0.3.2 → v0.3.3](https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff-pre-commit/compare/v0.3.2...v0.3.3)
- [github.com/PyCQA/autoflake: v2.3.0 → v2.3.1](https://github.com/PyCQA/autoflake/compare/v2.3.0...v2.3.1)

Correctly handle closing a file descriptor

- could have closed the wrong fd
- fixes #988

Fix incorrect exception on opening non-existing directory

- fixes #986

Add support for fake os.dup, os.dup2 and os.lseek

- closes #970

Fix handling of umask

- umask is now applied per default

Fix permission handling for opening file via file descriptor

- fixes #967

Remove the need to import the "undefined" module in test

- the module is not maintained and very trivial

Fix problem with shutil.rmtree if emulating Windows under POSIX

- the fd functions that are used for rmtree are not available under Windows
-> switched of the usage of these function in the fake fs
- fixes #979

Fix handling of missing attribute in os.getxattr

- no tests for real OS (extended atributes not enabled in CI)
- fixes #971

[pre-commit.ci] auto fixes from pre-commit.com hooks

for more information, see https://pre-commit.ci

[pre-commit.ci] pre-commit autoupdate

updates:
- [github.com/astral-sh/ruff-pre-commit: v0.2.0 → v0.3.2](https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff-pre-commit/compare/v0.2.0...v0.3.2)
- [github.com/pre-commit/mirrors-mypy: v1.8.0 → v1.9.0](https://github.com/pre-commit/mirrors-mypy/compare/v1.8.0...v1.9.0)

Add support for O_DIRECTORY and O_NOFOLLOW flags

- flags are considered in os.open if present

Add missing follow_symlink argument to os.link

- fixes #973

Fix incorrect handling of dirfd in os.symlink

- also removed check for supported dirfd where not used
- changed dirfd tests to run both in the fake and real OS
- fixed #968

Make sure the temp directory can be created during fs reset

We cannot use the `tempdir` module to get the temp directory
at that point, if the root dir is not writable by all.
This is a consequence of the fixes fo file permission handling.

Troubleshooting guide: add dynamic patcher problem handling

- add basic description of the module cleanup hooks

Remove the "module_cleanup_mode" argument from Patcher

- had been introduced in the previous patch release
  as a stop-gap measure for problems with django
- superseded by module cleanup handlers
Add chapter about nested fake filesystems to troubleshouting guide

Correctly handle file permissions for different classes

- always consider the current user group while evaluating
  file permissions for user/group/other classes

Use locale.getencoding instead of getpreferredencoding

- from Python 3.11 on, this is the preferred version
- fixes #957

Replace black and flake 8 with ruff

- adapt formatting where needed

Use cleanup hook to reload django views

- reload only the django view modules instead of all modules
- change the module cleanup mode default to always delete modules
  (avoiding problems with reloading other modules)
- closes #932

Add possibility to add a cleanup hook to modules

- may be needed for modules that cannot cleanly reload
- used for pandas.core.arrays.arrow.extension_types, see #947
Update pandas from 2.2.0 to 2.2.1
